IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO CENTRALIZE THE DELIVERY OF EMERGENCY SERVICES BY PROVIDING FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, FOOD, CLOTHING, INFORMATION AND REFERRAL TO RESIDENTS OF EASTERN HENRICO COUNTY, VIRGINIA, THEREBY REDUCING AN IMMEDIATE THREAT OF HOMELESSNESS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO CENTRALIZE THE DELIVERY OF EMERGENCY SERVICES BY PROVIDING FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, FOOD, CLOTHING, INFORMATION AND REFERRAL TO RESIDENTS OF EASTERN HENRICO COUNTY, VIRGINIA, THEREBY REDUCING AN IMMEDIATE THREAT OF HOMELESSNESS.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDE EMERGENCY FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO RESIDENTS OF EASTERN HENRICO COUNTY, VIRGINIA, EXPERIENCING HARDSHIPS. PAYMENTS WERE MADE ON BEHALF OF OUR APPROVED CLIENTS FOR RENT, MORTGAGE AND UTILITIES. IN 2020, THOSE PAYMENTS TOTALED $13,796.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: PROVIDE SPACE FOR CLOTHING AND HOUSEHOLD CLOSET TO PROVIDE ASSISTANCE FOR RESIDENTS OF HENRICO COUNTY, VIRGINIA, EXPERIENCING HARDSHIPS. IN 2020, 2,844 ITEMS WERE DONATED BY LOCAL CHURCHES, INDIVIDUALS AND SERVICE ORGANIZATIONS. THOSE 2,844 ITEMS WERE DISTRIBUTED TO APPROVED CLIENTS AND THEY WERE VALUED AT $8,532.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: PROVIDE SPACE FOR A FOOD PANTRY TO PROVIDE ASSISTANCE FOR RESIDENTS OF EASTERN HENRICO COUNTY, VIRGINIA, EXPERIENCING HARDSHIPS. IN 2020, 701 GROCERY BAGS OF FOOD WERE DONATED BY LOCAL CHURCHES, INDIVIDUALS AND SERVICE ORGINIZATIONS. THOSE 701 GROCERY BAGS WERE DISTRIBUTED TO APPROVED CLIENTS AND THEY WERE VALUED AT $24,535.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: Program expenses of Director's salary ($44,605); commercial answering service for clients ($2,808); office expenses ($1,194); Information/Technology ($2,504); travel expenses for Director ($21)

IRS990ScheduleA.FactsAndCircumstancesTestTxt: PART B, LINE10-"OTHER INCOME" INCLUDES CONTRIBUTIONS FROM LOCAL CHURCHES, INDIVIDUALS, SERVICE ORGANIZATIONS, FUNDRAISING EVENTS AND OTHER GRANTS.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: Line 10 represents Federated Campaigns amounts of $78, all other contributions, gifts, grants and similar amounts not included above of $42,870, and net fundraising income of $20,246.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Director's share of Health Care Costs had been withheld from December's pay; it was refunded to her as her insurance coverage changed for January 2021.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: Direct Financial Assistance on behalf of approved clients to vendors for client's utility bills, rent and or mortgage payments.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Part 1 Line 2 The executive Director evaluates the information provided by the client, vendors, and other service organizations to determine the client's need(s). Payment history, past assistance, and ability to maintain the household are also considered. Assistance is in the form of cash payments are made to vendors on behalf of the client. Part 3 Line 1 Payments were made on behalf of approved clients for rent, mortgage and utility bills. No client received over $500 in assistance.

The FISH clothing and household goods closet distributed 2,844 items (valued at $8,023) to clients. Food was donated and distributed to clients. A total of 701 bags of food (valued at $24,535) were distributed. Volunteers donated 3,101 hours (valued at $68,656) to the FISH organization. A local bank and individuals donated Christmas items to FISH which were distributed to 31 children (valued at $8,525).
Eastern Henrico FISH Inc (FISH) has no subordinates. It is all one entity.
FISH has been serving the residents of eastern Henrico County, VA since 1971. FISH incorporated in 2004.
The $1165 is the indirect cost for fundraising as the direct fundraising is reported on Form 990, page 9, part VII, line 8b less direct expenses.
In 2020, FISH paid $13,796 in financial assistance on behalf of approved clients.
FISH had no gaming (gambling) to prize winners.
FISH had no unrelated business income.
FISH had no indoor tanning services.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 8b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Our committees make reports to the Board at the monthly Board meetings and therefore their reports are included in the Board meeting minutes.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The FISH Finance Committee Chairman uses Schedules of Revenues, Expenses and assets from the FISH financial system to make a draft form of the 990 and required schedules. The Finance Committee reviews the draft Form 990 and related schedules. Changes are suggested. Necessary changes are made and the final Form 990 and related schedules are produced, signed and filed with the IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FISH's financial documents are provided to all Board members on a monthly basis. Board members share those financial documents with their respective churches. Governing documents and FISH's conflict of interest policy are available upon request.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Line (7) - Board member alternate. FISH bylaws allow two Board Members per member church; however, Board Member alternates are recognized should one of the two Board Members from that church not be able to attend a FISH Board meeting.
Fundraising revenues are zero dollars here; fundraising revenues are reported on 8a.
All fundraising revenues ($26,291) are reported here.
In 2020, FISH reported $13,796 in financial assistance on behalf of approved clients.
The $1,723 is the net increase in "restricted use" funds.

ReasonableCauseExplanation.ExplanationTxt: The organization submitted a paper copy of Form 990 postmarked November 15, 2021, which was the extended due date. In April, we received a letter from the IRS along with the paper copy of the Form 990 which indicated the IRS would not be able to accept the filing as it was not submitted electronically. Due to the pandemic and a health issue of one of the main preparers of the Form 990, our volunteers were experiencing issues getting the form prepared electronically as they had not used that system prior. We ask for your understanding in this matter. We at FISH are aware of the importance of timely submissions of Form 990 as evidenced by our past filings. We are working diligently to update and maintain all filings in a timely manner.
